</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A4B3EFB8E903FFA9FF1CFBBAFC50FBD9" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="EC16BC33E903FFA9FF1CFBBAFC50FBD9" blockId="49.[120,1225,225,1335]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
ETYMOLOGY: Patronym, for Julian Stark, dipterologist, colleague, and friend of the author, who collaborated in fieldwork in 
<collectingCountry id="94BEFCA3E903FFA9FDB6FBE7FD02FBD9" box="[514,692,1121,1147]" name="Dominican Republic" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">the Dominican</collectingCountry>
Republic and 
<collectingCountry id="94BEFCA3E903FFA9FCD4FBE4FC54FBD9" box="[864,994,1121,1148]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A4B3EFB8E903FFA9FF1CFB01FBDBFA94" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EC16BC33E903FFA9FF1CFB01FBDBFA94" blockId="49.[120,1225,225,1335]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<materialsCitation id="5CC1B66EE903FFA9FF1CFB01FBDFFA94" country="Dominican Republic" location="Moreover" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" specimenCount="1">
COMMENTS: The male genitalia of the 
<typeStatus id="33120291E903FFA9FDD5FB01FD25FB03" box="[609,659,1159,1185]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">type</typeStatus>
and only specimen of this species are unique for the 
<taxonomicName id="2BA9C7B0E903FFA9FF17FB2AFEA7FB64" box="[163,273,1196,1222]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Psathyrellaceae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="bromeliae">
<emphasis id="DEDD6021E903FFA9FF17FB2AFEA7FB64" box="[163,273,1196,1222]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">bromeliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group: the aedeagus is short and straight, with a very slender base; the distiphallus is bulbous, with extensive membrane and a ventral shelf bearing a pair of spines; gonopod and surstylus are relatively small, and the aedeagal apodeme is large. 
<location id="E976EAE8E903FFA9FCDEFB71FC6DFAB3" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:64000D25E91DFFA9FE5EF9CFFBDBFA94:E976EAE8E903FFA9FCDEFB71FC6DFAB3" box="[874,987,1271,1297]" country="Dominican Republic" name="Moreover" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Moreover</location>
, it was not collected at flowers, but by sweeping the muddy shores of a river in eastern 
<collectingCountry id="94BEFCA3E903FFA9FCC2FA9AFBDFFA94" box="[886,1129,1308,1334]" name="Dominican Republic" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Dominican Republic</collectingCountry>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
